{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"Attestation manifests (plan-review and completion-verifier) should record the\n**version of rebar that produced the certification**, for audit/provenance —\n*not* for enforcement. `regver` (criteria-registry version) already owns\nversion-skew invalidation; this stamp is never read by `compute_validity` and\nnever auto-invalidates an attestation.\n\n## Context\n\n- Signed manifests are built by `build_manifest` (plan-review) and\n  `_verdict_manifest` (completion-verifier) in `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/attest.py`.\n- The manifest already carries a `regver:` line (enforced skew stamp) and, for\n  plan-review, `verified_at_sha` (the **target** repo SHA). The new stamp is a\n  distinct axis: which **rebar gate code** signed the attestation.\n- Package version is **static** (`pyproject.toml` `version = \"0.6.0\"`, hatchling,\n  no VCS) — coarse, so version alone can't answer \"what code certified this?\".\n  Hence version **+ short commit SHA of the gate-code checkout**.\n\n## What gets recorded\n\nOne additive manifest line, e.g. `rebar-version: 0.6.0 (gc1a2b3c4-dirty)`:\n- **Version**: `rebar.__version__` (static package version).\n- **Commit SHA** of the **rebar source (gate code)** checkout — NOT the target\n  repo — resolved **live-first, baked-second**:\n  1. live git checkout of the rebar source -> `git -C <dir of rebar.__file__>\n     rev-parse --short HEAD` (dev/editable: the live truth, wins over any baked\n     value which goes stale as you commit);\n  2. else -> SHA **baked at build time** into a generated, git-ignored\n     `src/rebar/_build_info.py` (PyPI/wheel install);\n  3. else -> omit the SHA, keep the version.\n- **`-dirty` marker** on the live-checkout path when the working tree has\n  uncommitted changes (`git status --porcelain`), so a mid-edit signer can't\n  stamp a clean SHA that doesn't match the running gate code. Release builds are\n  clean.\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- An auditor reading a signed attestation can determine the exact rebar version\n  and (where a checkout or release build exists) the gate-code commit that\n  produced it, across dev/editable and PyPI installs.\n- Zero behavior change to gate validity: the stamp never affects claim/close.\n\n## Scope / non-goals\n\n- No enforcement / no auto-invalidation on version mismatch (that stays with\n  `regver`).\n- Version stays static; do NOT switch to hatch-vcs — only add SHA capture.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `build_manifest` (plan-review) and `_verdict_manifest`\n      (completion-verifier) both append a `rebar-version:` line carrying the\n      static version + short gate-code commit SHA.\n- [ ] A SHA-resolution helper implements live-git-first, build-baked-second,\n      omit-last, with a `-dirty` suffix when the live checkout is dirty.\n- [ ] A hatchling build hook (`BuildHookInterface`) captures the commit SHA at\n      wheel/sdist build into a generated, git-ignored `src/rebar/_build_info.py`;\n      absent-git build omits it gracefully.\n- [ ] A `manifest_rebar_version()` parser (mirroring `manifest_regver()`)\n      extracts the stamp; returns `None` for pre-stamp manifests.\n- [ ] `compute_validity` is unchanged and never reads the stamp; old manifests\n      without the line still validate byte-identically.\n- [ ] The stamp is surfaced in `show` (attestation block) and returned by\n      `verify_signature`.\n- [ ] Tests: both manifests carry the line; live-checkout resolution (incl.\n      `-dirty`); baked fallback for non-git install; graceful omit; parser\n      round-trip + pre-stamp `None`; no validity impact."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783122940905906001,"uuid":"dcb699bb-afbe-4353-9a4f-ba5aa168a1dd"}